# Yarn (classic) treats engine mismatches as hard errors. A transitive dev
# dependency (@achrinza/node-ipc, pulled in by the legacy @vue/cli toolchain)
# declares support only up to Node 19, which breaks `yarn install` on the
# Node 22 CI runner used by Azure Static Web Apps / Oryx. The package runs
# fine on newer Node, so ignore the over-restrictive engine check.
--ignore-engines true
